{"user_message": {"title": "Architecture Review — Highest-Priority Correctness Defect in case-file (ADR 0002)", "content": "## ADR 0002 — Make criteria row tone status-safe and derive counts from data\n\n**Scope:** `src/features/case-file` · extends ADR 0001 · published to `docs/adr/0002-criteria-row-tone-and-derived-counts.md`\n\n### Context\nADR 0001 removed the unsafe `status !== \"Partial\" → qualifying` assumption from the **summary badge** and centralized counting in `summarizeCriteria()` (verified sound: 7 qualifying · 1 partial · 8 evaluated). Reviewing the same surface, that assumption **survives in two places in `CriteriaTable.tsx`**:\n\n1. **Highest-priority defect — per-row tone (`CriteriaTable.tsx:7`):**\n   ```tsx\n   function toneFor(status) { return status === \"Partial\" ? \"warning\" : \"success\"; }\n   ```\n   Any non-`Partial` value — including an **unknown/absent status from upstream Document AI / Gemini scoring** (the exact threat ADR 0001 names) — renders a **green `success` badge**. But `summarizeCriteria` *excludes* that same row. So the table paints an unscored criterion as \"met\" while the eligibility count silently drops it — **table and summary disagree on a legal eligibility surface.**\n2. **Related robustness gap (`CriteriaTable.tsx:18,21`):** `{summary.total} of 8 evaluated` and `Need 3 to qualify` hardcode `8` (decoupled from `criteria.length`) and `3` (decoupled from `QUALIFYING_THRESHOLD`). A 9th criterion renders \"9 of 8 evaluated\".\n\n`format.ts` was inspected and is unused/sound for current inputs — not the defect.\n\n### Decision\nExtend ADR 0001's centralization to the row level: add an exhaustive, runtime-guarded `statusTone(status)` to `criteria.ts` (`Partial→warning`, `Met|Strong→success`, **unknown/absent→neutral, never green**); wire `CriteriaTable` row badges to it; replace hardcoded `8` with `criteria.length` and `3` with `QUALIFYING_THRESHOLD`. Engineer owns the fix + regression test.\n\n### Consequences\n- Table and summary can no longer disagree; malformed rows render neutral, not green.\n- Read-out tracks data + threshold constant as criteria evolve.\n- **Rendering preserved for current data** (8 criteria, threshold 3, all rows Met/Strong/Partial → identical output); pinned by regression test + `tsc --noEmit`.\n- Extends, does not contradict, ADR 0001.\n\n---\n\n## Task Breakdown — 4 tasks · 7 story points\n\n| # | Task | Scope | Points |\n|---|------|-------|--------|\n| 1 | Add `statusTone()` to `criteria.ts` | Exhaustive map Met/Strong→success, Partial→warning, fallback→neutral; runtime-guarded (no type-only reliance); exported | 2 |\n| 2 | Wire `CriteriaTable.tsx` | Replace inline `toneFor` with `statusTone`; denominator `criteria.length`; threshold text from `QUALIFYING_THRESHOLD` | 2 |\n| 3 | Regression test (`criteria.test.ts`) | Pin current render (7/1/8, success); assert unknown/absent status → not `success`; denominator tracks data length | 2 |\n| 4 | Verify rendering preserved | `tsc --noEmit` + `tsx --test` green; confirm current-data badges/counts unchanged | 1 |\n\n```chart\nRow-tone safety fix: 2\nDerived counts wiring: 2\nRegression test: 2\nVerification: 1\n```\n\n**Verdict:** Change fits the current architecture (direct extension of ADR 0001's pattern). Low risk, rendering-preserving. Ready for a delivery agent — `architecture.analysis.completed` emitted.", "content_type": "success", "priority": "high"}}

