{"user_message": {"title": "Code Review — APPROVE: criteria row tone status-safe + derived counts (ADR 0002, commit 207626e)", "content": "## Code Review — APPROVE (with notes)\n\n**Changeset:** `207626e` — *fix(case-file): make criteria row tone status-safe + derive counts (ADR 0002)*\n**Scope reviewed:** `criteria.ts`, `components/CriteriaTable.tsx`, `criteria.test.ts`, `package.json`\n\nThis change extends ADR 0001's eligibility-safety principle from the summary badge down to the per-row badge. Reviewed across security, correctness, and quality; verified empirically (tests + typecheck).\n\n### Critical\n_None._\n\n### High\n_None._\n\n### Medium\n_None._\n\n### Low / Notes\n- `criteria.test.ts:48` — the no-regression test re-derives the expected tone with the same formula it's testing (`c.status === \"Partial\" ? \"warning\" : \"success\"`) rather than asserting literal expectations. A Met/Strong→neutral regression would still be caught by the `neutral===0` count and the dedicated unknown-status test, so coverage holds — but **fix:** assert per-status literals (`statusTone(\"Met\") === \"success\"`, etc.) so the pin doesn't depend on the implementation's own branching.\n- `CriteriaTable.tsx:13` — header now reads `{summary.total} of {criteria.length} evaluated`. When a row is malformed, `summary.total < criteria.length`, so the two numbers can differ. This is **intentional and honest** (\"evaluated\" = well-formed rows; denominator = rows present), not a defect — flagged only so the semantics are on record.\n\n### Why this is correct\n- `statusTone(status: unknown)` runtime-guards AI-sourced data instead of trusting the `CriterionStatus` type: `Partial → warning`, `Met|Strong → success`, **everything else → neutral**. `BadgeTone` (`src/components/ui/Badge.tsx:4`) includes `neutral`, so all returns are valid.\n- Tone logic now agrees with `summarizeCriteria` by construction — a row the summary excludes renders `neutral`, never green. **ADR 0002 invariant preserved: an unscored criterion cannot paint as \"met\".** Table and summary can no longer disagree on a legal-eligibility surface.\n- Hardcoded `8`/`3` replaced by `criteria.length` / `QUALIFYING_THRESHOLD` — read-out tracks data and threshold.\n\n### Verification (empirical)\n| Check | Result |\n|---|---|\n| `npx tsx --test src/**/*.test.ts` | ✅ 8/8 pass |\n| `tsc --noEmit` | ✅ clean |\n| ADR 0002 invariant (unknown ≠ success) | ✅ asserted + passes |\n\n### Adjacent (out of scope — not part of this verdict)\n- **BL-001** (case-file UI coupled to the single-case `data.ts` fixture) is a separate, still-untriaged candidate. Not introduced by this change; tracked in the knowledge graph as `decision-case-file-data-source-seam`. Reviewed independently when/if implemented.\n\n---\n**Verdict: APPROVE** — no critical, security, or correctness issues; only low-severity test-hygiene notes. Review completed in full (files read, tests run, typecheck clean)."}, "content_type": "success", "priority": "normal"}

